  "texts": [
    "As parallel (AMR, text) data only exists for a restricted set of languages, we use both machine translation and AMR-parsing to create multilingual training and test data.",
    "Training Data.",
    "The AMR 3.0 dataset (Knight, Kevin et al., 2020) 3 includes 55.6K (gold AMR, 3 https://catalog.ldc.upenn.edu/LDC2020T02 human-written text) pairs where the texts are in English.",
    "We create training data for our target languages using machine translation and language identification scores as follows.",
    "First, we translate the English texts to our target languages using a 4-bit quantized NLLB-3.3B model (NLLB Team et al., 2022) 4."
